    "asOf": "2022-06-13",
    "date": "2022-10-18T15:02:02Z",
    "text": "Formula Shortage Reporting Act of 2022\n\nThis bill requires manufacturers of infant formula to notify the Food and Drug Administration (FDA) at least 72 hours in advance of a manufacturing interruption or product discontinuance that is expected to meaningfully disrupt the product's supply. The FDA must post such information on its website and notify health care providers."
